s `resource:/...`, and Camel’s `DefaultPackageScanResourceResolver` cannot walk that protocol as a jar or directory, so `findResources(\\\".../*-check\\\")` returns `0` even though the specific descriptor file is present and readable. That means the last failure is a Camel package-scan limitation under native image, not a remaining missing metadata entry.\\n\\nI left `tests/src/org.apache.camel/camel-health/4.20.0/user-code-filter.json` untouched; it was already locally modified before I started.\"}}\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.apache.camel:camel-health:4.20.0/metadata-fix/codex.log:151:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_4\",\"type\":\"todo_list\",\"items\":[{\"text\":\"Reproduce the camel-health 4.20.0 test failure with the required GraalVM environment\",\"completed\":true},{\"text\":\"Patch reachability metadata based on the failing access stack and condition timing\",\"completed\":true},{\"text\":\"Re-run the targeted test until it passes and summarize the fix\",\"completed\":false}]}}\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.apache.camel:camel-health:4.20.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-06-28T07-25-25-090308Z.log:29:  - Every individual test must complete in under 60 seconds. Use bounded waits and short client/server/executor timeouts, close all resources, and avoid sleeps or background work that can deadlock or keep the JVM alive.\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.apache.camel:camel-health:4.20.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-06-28T07-25-25-090308Z.log:35:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_start\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Role: You are an expert JVM test engineer specializing in high-coverage integration testing for external libraries.\\n\\nTask:\\nYou need to generate comprehensive tests for the library defined by these Maven coordinates: org.apache.camel:camel-health:4.20.0.\\n\\nIssue-Requested Metadata:\\nNo reporter-provided missing metadata context was supplied.\\n\\nLibrary Pre